<img src="line-201.gif" width="526" height="20"></center><ul>

<H2><IMG SRC="marker2.gif"><I><A name="1"> <font color="#004080">Women</font></A></I></H2>
<UL><DL><P>
<dt><font size="+1">W</font>OMEN have no wilderness in them,
<dt>They are provident instead,
<dt>Content in the tight hot cell of their hearts
<dt>To eat dusty bread.
<p>
<dt>They do not see cattle cropping red winter grass,
<dt>They do not hear
<dt>Snow water going down under culverts
<dt>Shallow and clear.
<p>
<dt>They wait, when they should turn to journeys,
<dt>They stiffen, when they should bend.
<dt>They use against themselves that benevolence
<dt>To which no man is friend.
<p>
<dt>They cannot think of so many crops to a field
<dt>Or of clean wood cleft by an axe.
<dt>Their love is an eager meaninglessness
<dt>Too tense or too lax.
<p>
<dt>They hear in any whisper that speaks to them
<dt>A shout and a cry.
<dt>As like as not, when they take life over their door-sill
<dt>They should let it go by.
<P><DD><b>Louise Bogan</b></DL></UL><p>

